[1] Cholera - Angola (Luanda)
Date: Tue 7 Aug 2018
Source: Observador [machine trans. edited]
https://observador.pt/2018/08/07/colera-matou-seis-pessoas-de-86-suspeitos-em-luanda-desde-maio/


Cholera has killed 6 people in Angola since May 2018, with 12 cases confirmed among the 86 suspected cases registered to date, only in the province of Luanda, the health authorities said on Tue 7 Aug 2018.

The data were forwarded to the Lusa agency by the provincial director of Luanda, Rosa Bessa, after a meeting of the Provincial Committee to Combat Endemics, which analyzed the disease situation in the capital of Angola.

According to Rosa Bessa, the Inter-ministerial Commission and the Province of Luanda have joined efforts to combat the disease that, in the last 4 months caused, according to data from the Ministry of Health, 6 deaths of the 12 cases, which were laboratory confirmed. "It is also necessary to take appropriate measures at home and consume water after boiling or disinfecting with bleach as preventive measures," said Rosa Bessa.

Other outbreaks of cholera also affected the provinces of Uíge and Cabinda in 2018, both in northern Angola, the 1st of which sickened more than 600 people and caused more than a dozen deaths, and 2nd over 10 cases with at least one death registered last February 2018.

Poor basic sanitation and the use of contaminated water are causes indicated by the health authorities for the appearance of these outbreaks.

