[2] Cholera - Niger (Marandi)
Date: Mon 23 Jul 2018
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/niger-four-dead-123-cases-latest-cholera-outbreak-51246/


The government of Niger says 4 people have died while 123 cases are being monitored following the outbreak of cholera in the Maradi region on [13 Jul 2018]. The outbreak is concentrated in the Madarounfa district, which sits on the border with Nigeria. The deceased were members of the same family, who recently returned from a long stay in Katsina state, Nigeria. They presented symptoms that included diarrhea, vomiting, and dehydration.

"Laboratory results released by the Centre for Medical and Health Research (CERMES) in Niamey on 12 Jul 2018 confirmed _Vibrio cholerae_ O1 Inaba in samples from the 3 case patients. A retrospective investigation found that the patients developed symptoms in the village of Makada in Jibiya local government area in Nigeria prior to admission at the health centre in Niger," the Ministry of Public Health said.

Between 6 and 7 Jul 2018], 6 new cases from 3 villages close to the border with Nigeria were confirmed. They all presented similar signs and symptoms to those of the deceased cases. At least 19 out of the 123 cases under treatment are villagers from the Nigerian side of the border.

[byline: Oscar Nikala]

