[4] Cholera - Saudi Arabia (Asir region)
Date: Wed 25 Jul 2018 14:20 AST
Source: Okaz News [in Arabic, trans. Mod.MM, edited]
https://bit.ly/2LNp8Xv


In a press release, the Ministry of Health of Asir region reported that 22 cases of acute watery diarrhea were admitted at Alfarsha General Hospital. After initial lab investigations, 15 cases were confirmed as cholera, while 7 others await further confirmation. All the cholera cases were related to illegal immigrants of African origin, and they were hospitalized and given the needed appropriate care, according to the MoH statement.

